dismissalText.commentary: Abdullah Shafique c Pope b Atkinson 102 (184b 10x4 2x6 265m) SR: 55.43

dismissalComment.html: tired shot, straight to cover! Atkinson gets his second of the day, and ends a 56-over shutout by Pakistan's second-wicket pair. The heat probably gets an assist. England went with a ring field and just hung the ball in the channel, and it didn't take long for Shafique to push one on the up straight to a fielder. He drags himself off, eager for a drink but knowing he's missed a chance for a daddy

dismissalText.commentary: Shan Masood c & b Leach 151 (177b 13x4 2x6 260m) SR: 85.31

dismissalComment.html: chipped back to the bowler, one brings two! Bit of drift and drop from Leach and Masood's drive is skewed off the inside half of the bat for a simple return catch. First Test wicket since Hyderabad in January for Leach. Again a hint of fatigue in the shot, the end of a fine innings from Masood. England have gone bang-bang since tea and got rid of both centurions

dismissalText.commentary: Saud Shakeel c Root b Shoaib Bashir 82 (177b 8x4 0x6 274m) SR: 46.32

dismissalComment.html: beautifully bowled, a wicket from nowhere! Drop and turn, leg stump to off, feathers the edge... and ends up in the hands of slip! Shakeel was defending but couldn't cover the spin. Think it brushed the back leg, which bypassed Smith, but Root was alert for the catch.
